# No Raw Tailwind in Governed UI

## Story files (`*.stories.tsx`)

Stories **must not** contain raw spacing or arbitrary-value utilities in
static `className="..."` strings. Use story layout primitives instead.

| Forbidden | Use instead |
|-----------|-------------|
| `className="mt-3 mb-2"` | wrap siblings in `<StoryStack gap="md">` |
| `className="p-4"` | `<StoryStack padding="lg">` or `<StoryFrame padding="lg">` |
| `className="px-4 py-2"` | `<StoryRow paddingX="lg" paddingY="sm">` |
| `className="w-[200px]"` | add a `width` prop to `StoryFrame` or use `max-w-sm` etc. |

```tsx
// âťŚ BAD â€” raw spacing in story
<div className="flex items-center justify-between p-4 mt-3">

// âś… GOOD â€” story layout primitives
<StoryStack padding="lg" gap="md">
  <StoryRow justify="between">
```

**Allowed** in stories: layout helpers (`flex`, `grid`, `gap-*`, `items-*`,
`justify-*`, `max-w-*`, `w-full`, `overflow-*`, `rounded-*`, `border-*`,
`font-*`, `text-*`, `bg-*` that reference semantic tokens).

## Governed component files (`*.tsx`, not stories)

Component source must never contain raw Tailwind. All styling goes through the
governance API.

| Forbidden | Use instead |
|-----------|-------------|
| `bg-red-500`, `text-blue-700` | `tone` / `intent` prop â†’ recipe |
| `rounded-md`, `shadow-lg` | `radius` / `shadow` governed prop |
| `bg-primary`, `text-muted-foreground` | `resolvePrimitiveGovernance` result |
| `text-[13px]`, `rounded-[8px]` | token value in recipe |
| local `cva(...)` | use `recipeName` + design-system recipe map |

```tsx
// âťŚ BAD â€” raw semantic Tailwind in a governed component
<div className="rounded-md bg-primary text-primary-foreground px-3 py-1">

// âś… GOOD â€” governed presentation
const governed = resolvePrimitiveGovernance(props);
return (
  <div {...governed.dataAttributes} className={governed.classes.root}>
```

## `story-frame.tsx` is the single exception

`_storybook/story-frame.tsx` is the **designated centraliser** of raw layout
Tailwind for story composition. It may use `flex`, `gap-*`, `p-*`, `max-w-*`,
etc. No other file in `packages/ui/src/components` may do so.

Do not duplicate these utilities by adding a new `className="..."` string to
a story; instead, add a prop to `StoryFrame`, `StoryStack`, or `StoryRow`.

---

## Consumer packages (`packages/appshell`, `apps/erp`)

This rule covers the **author** layer (`packages/ui/src/components/`).

For consuming `@afenda/ui` primitives in shell composition, a separate rule applies:
â†’ **`.cursor/rules/governed-ui-consumption.mdc`**

Key difference: consumers are allowed to use token utilities on **plain HTML**
(`div`, `span`, `header`, etc.) sourced from `globals.css`. What they must
**never** do is pass `className` to a governed `@afenda/ui` component â€” that
is caught by the consumer rule, not this one.

Static enforcement for both layers runs via:
- `pnpm --filter @afenda/ui check:governance` (author)
- `pnpm --filter @afenda/appshell check:governance` (appshell consumer)
- `pnpm --filter @afenda/erp test:run` (erp consumer, includes static test)
